title: Nicki Minaj's Remy Ma Diss Track "No Frauds" Isn't So Much Of A Diss Track, According To Twitter
text:
24 
Twitter – Finally, Nicki Minaj released a reply to Remy Ma dragging on her “SHETHER” with “No Frauds” featuring her Young Money compadres Lil Wayne and Drake, plus dropping two other joints “Changed It” featuring Weezy and a ballad titled “Regret In Your Tears,” dubbing it the #3PackFromParis. 
Of course, Twitter has reacted to Nicki’s slowly addressed response ( that reportedly almost never happened ) to Remy’s now regretful release of a diss track with dullness. HipHopDX’s Justin Hunte even gave a few brainy reasons why Nicki Minaj shouldn’t even respond to Remy while our editor-in-chief Trent Clark expounded on how Rem missed her chance by using the instrumental to Nas’“Ether” to prove her point. Why Nicki Minaj Should Not Respond To Remy Ma 
The general consensus on Twitter is that “No Frauds” is not a proper diss number, but it certainly is a bop. 
While some seem disappointed that Nick didn’t bite back as hard as Remy did, others are okay with the possibility that “No Frauds” will be 2017’s summer anthem. Much like Drizzy accomplished with the Meek Mill diss track “Back To Back.” "Back 2 Back?! Me and Drizzy laughed at that.."
